#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an3.57"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.57:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.57:0.2"
msgid "6. Brāhmaṇavagga "
msgstr "6. Brahmins "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.57:0.3"
msgid "57. Vacchagottasutta "
msgstr "57. With Vacchagotta "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.161, sc1
#. VAR: vacchagotto → vacchaputto (mr)
msgctxt "an3.57:1.1"
msgid "Atha kho vacchagotto paribbājako yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi. "
msgstr "Then the wanderer Vacchagotta went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him. "

msgctxt "an3.57:1.2"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho vacchagotto paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to the Buddha: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.57:1.3"
msgid "“sutaṃ metaṃ, bho gotama, samaṇo gotamo evamāha: "
msgstr "“I have heard, Master Gotama, that the ascetic Gotama says this: "

msgctxt "an3.57:1.4"
msgid "‘mayhameva dānaṃ dātabbaṃ, nāññesaṃ dānaṃ dātabbaṃ; "
msgstr "‘Gifts should only be given to me, not to others. "

msgctxt "an3.57:1.5"
msgid "mayhameva sāvakānaṃ dānaṃ dātabbaṃ, nāññesaṃ sāvakānaṃ dānaṃ dātabbaṃ; "
msgstr "Gifts should only be given to my disciples, not to the disciples of others. "

msgctxt "an3.57:1.6"
msgid "mayhameva dinnaṃ mahapphalaṃ, nāññesaṃ dinnaṃ mahapphalaṃ; "
msgstr "Only what is given to me is very fruitful, not what is given to others. "

msgctxt "an3.57:1.7"
msgid "mayhameva sāvakānaṃ dinnaṃ mahapphalaṃ, nāññesaṃ sāvakānaṃ dinnaṃ mahapphalan’ti. "
msgstr "Only what is given to my disciples is very fruitful, not what is given to the disciples of others.’ "

msgctxt "an3.57:1.8"
msgid "Ye te, bho gotama, evamāhaṃsu ‘samaṇo gotamo evamāha: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.57:1.9"
msgid "“mayhameva dānaṃ dātabbaṃ, nāññesaṃ dānaṃ dātabbaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.57:1.10"
msgid "Mayhameva sāvakānaṃ dānaṃ dātabbaṃ, nāññesaṃ sāvakānaṃ dānaṃ dātabbaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.57:1.11"
msgid "Mayhameva dinnaṃ mahapphalaṃ, nāññesaṃ dinnaṃ mahapphalaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.57:1.12"
msgid "Mayhameva sāvakānaṃ dinnaṃ mahapphalaṃ, nāññesaṃ sāvakānaṃ dinnaṃ mahapphalan”’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: vādānupāto → vādānuvādo (mr)
msgctxt "an3.57:1.13"
msgid "Kacci te bhoto gotamassa vuttavādino na ca bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ abhūtena abbhācikkhanti, dhammassa cānudhammaṃ byākaronti, na ca koci sahadhammiko vādānupāto gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ āgacchati? "
msgstr "I trust that those who say this repeat what the Buddha has said, and do not misrepresent him with an untruth? Is their explanation in line with the teaching? Are there any legitimate grounds for rebuke and criticism? "

msgctxt "an3.57:1.14"
msgid "Anabbhakkhātukāmā hi mayaṃ bhavantaṃ gotaman”ti. "
msgstr "For we don’t want to misrepresent Master Gotama.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an3.57:2.1"
msgid "“Ye te, vaccha, evamāhaṃsu: "
msgstr "“Vaccha, those who say this "

msgctxt "an3.57:2.2"
msgid "‘samaṇo gotamo evamāha: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.57:2.3"
msgid "“mayhameva dānaṃ dātabbaṃ … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.57:2.4"
msgid "nāññesaṃ sāvakānaṃ dinnaṃ mahapphalan”’ti "
msgstr " "

#. VAR: ca pana maṃ → ca pana maṃ te (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.57:2.5"
msgid "na me te vuttavādino. Abbhācikkhanti ca pana maṃ asatā abhūtena. "
msgstr "do not repeat what I have said. They misrepresent me with what is false and untrue. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.57:2.6"
msgid "Yo kho, vaccha, paraṃ dānaṃ dadantaṃ vāreti so tiṇṇaṃ antarāyakaro hoti, tiṇṇaṃ pāripanthiko. "
msgstr "Anyone who prevents another from giving makes an obstacle and a barrier for three people. "

msgctxt "an3.57:2.7"
msgid "Katamesaṃ tiṇṇaṃ? "
msgstr "What three? "

msgctxt "an3.57:2.8"
msgid "Dāyakassa puññantarāyakaro hoti, paṭiggāhakānaṃ lābhantarāyakaro hoti, pubbeva kho panassa attā khato ca hoti upahato ca. "
msgstr "The giver is obstructed from making merit. The receiver is obstructed from getting what is offered. And they’ve already broken and damaged themselves. "

msgctxt "an3.57:2.9"
msgid "Yo kho, vaccha, paraṃ dānaṃ dadantaṃ vāreti so imesaṃ tiṇṇaṃ antarāyakaro hoti, tiṇṇaṃ pāripanthiko. "
msgstr "Anyone who prevents another from giving makes an obstacle and a barrier for these three people. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an3.57:3.1"
msgid "Ahaṃ kho pana, vaccha, evaṃ vadāmi: "
msgstr "Vaccha, this is what I say: "

#. VAR: thālidhovanaṃ → thālakadhovanaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an3.57:3.2"
msgid "‘ye hi te candanikāya vā oligalle vā pāṇā, tatrapi yo thālidhovanaṃ vā sarāvadhovanaṃ vā chaḍḍeti: "
msgstr "‘You even make merit by tipping out dish-washing water in a cesspool or a sump with living creatures in it, thinking, "

msgctxt "an3.57:3.3"
msgid "“ye tattha pāṇā te tena yāpentū”’ti, tato nidānampāhaṃ, vaccha, puññassa āgamaṃ vadāmi. "
msgstr "“May any creatures here be nourished!”’ "

msgctxt "an3.57:3.4"
msgid "Ko pana vādo manussabhūte. "
msgstr "How much more then for human beings! "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.57:3.5"
msgid "Api cāhaṃ, vaccha, sīlavato dinnaṃ mahapphalaṃ vadāmi, no tathā dussīlassa, so ca hoti pañcaṅgavippahīno pañcaṅgasamannāgato. "
msgstr "However, I also say that a gift to an ethical person is more fruitful than one to an unethical person. They’ve given up five factors, and possess five factors. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.162, sc4
msgctxt "an3.57:4.1"
msgid "Katamāni pañcaṅgāni pahīnāni honti? "
msgstr "What are the five factors they’ve given up? "

msgctxt "an3.57:4.2"
msgid "Kāmacchando pahīno hoti, byāpādo pahīno hoti, thinamiddhaṃ pahīnaṃ hoti, uddhaccakukkuccaṃ pahīnaṃ hoti, vicikicchā pahīnā hoti. "
msgstr "Sensual desire, ill will, dullness and drowsiness, restlessness and remorse, and doubt. "

msgctxt "an3.57:4.3"
msgid "Imāni pañcaṅgāni vippahīnāni honti. "
msgstr "These are the five factors they’ve given up. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an3.57:5.1"
msgid "Katamehi pañcahi aṅgehi samannāgato hoti? "
msgstr "What are the five factors they possess? "

msgctxt "an3.57:5.2"
msgid "Asekkhena sīlakkhandhena samannāgato hoti, asekkhena samādhikkhandhena samannāgato hoti, asekkhena paññākkhandhena samannāgato hoti, asekkhena vimuttikkhandhena samannāgato hoti, asekkhena vimuttiñāṇadassanakkhandhena samannāgato hoti; "
msgstr "The entire spectrum of an adept’s ethics, immersion, wisdom, freedom, and knowledge and vision of freedom. "

msgctxt "an3.57:5.3"
msgid "imehi pañcahi aṅgehi samannāgato hoti. "
msgstr "These are the five factors they possess. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.57:5.4"
msgid "Iti pañcaṅgavippahīne pañcaṅgasamannāgate dinnaṃ mahapphalanti vadāmīti. "
msgstr "I say that a gift to anyone who has given up these five factors and possesses these five factors is very fruitful. "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an3.57:6.1"
msgid "Iti kaṇhāsu setāsu, "
msgstr "Cows may be black or white, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:6.2"
msgid "rohiṇīsu harīsu vā; "
msgstr "red or tawny, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:6.3"
msgid "Kammāsāsu sarūpāsu, "
msgstr "mottled or uniform, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:6.4"
msgid "gosu pārevatāsu vā. "
msgstr "or pigeon-colored. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "an3.57:7.1"
msgid "Yāsu kāsuci etāsu, "
msgstr "But when one is born among them, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:7.2"
msgid "danto jāyati puṅgavo; "
msgstr "the bull that’s tamed "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:7.3"
msgid "Dhorayho balasampanno, "
msgstr "—a behemoth, powerful, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:7.4"
msgid "kalyāṇajavanikkamo; "
msgstr "well-paced in pulling forward—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:7.5"
msgid "Tameva bhāre yuñjanti, "
msgstr "they yoke the load just to him, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:7.6"
msgid "nāssa vaṇṇaṃ parikkhare. "
msgstr "regardless of his color. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "an3.57:8.1"
msgid "Evamevaṃ manussesu, "
msgstr "So it is for humans, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:8.2"
msgid "yasmiṃ kasmiñci jātiye; "
msgstr "wherever they may be born "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:8.3"
msgid "Khattiye brāhmaṇe vesse, "
msgstr "—among aristocrats, brahmins, merchants, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:8.4"
msgid "sudde caṇḍālapukkuse. "
msgstr "workers, or outcastes and scavengers—"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "an3.57:9.1"
msgid "Yāsu kāsuci etāsu, "
msgstr "one is born among them, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:9.2"
msgid "danto jāyati subbato; "
msgstr "tamed, true to their vows. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:9.3"
msgid "Dhammaṭṭho sīlasampanno, "
msgstr "Firm in principle, accomplished in ethical conduct, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:9.4"
msgid "saccavādī hirīmano. "
msgstr "truthful, conscientious, "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "an3.57:10.1"
msgid "Pahīnajātimaraṇo, "
msgstr "they’ve given up birth and death. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:10.2"
msgid "brahmacariyassa kevalī; "
msgstr "Complete in the spiritual journey, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:10.3"
msgid "Pannabhāro visaṃyutto, "
msgstr "with burden put down, detached, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:10.4"
msgid "katakicco anāsavo. "
msgstr "they’ve completed the task and are free of defilements. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "an3.57:11.1"
msgid "Pāragū sabbadhammānaṃ, "
msgstr "Gone beyond all things, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:11.2"
msgid "anupādāya nibbuto; "
msgstr "they’re extinguished by not grasping. "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Tasmiṃyeva → tasmiṃ ve (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an3.57:11.3"
msgid "Tasmiṃyeva viraje khette, "
msgstr "In that flawless field, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:11.4"
msgid "vipulā hoti dakkhiṇā. "
msgstr "a religious donation is abundant. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "an3.57:12.1"
msgid "Bālā ca avijānantā, "
msgstr "Fools who don’t understand "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:12.2"
msgid "dummedhā assutāvino; "
msgstr "—stupid, uneducated—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:12.3"
msgid "Bahiddhā denti dānāni, "
msgstr "give their gifts to those outside, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:12.4"
msgid "na hi sante upāsare. "
msgstr "and don’t attend the peaceful ones. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "an3.57:13.1"
msgid "Ye ca sante upāsanti, "
msgstr "But those who do attend the peaceful ones "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:13.2"
msgid "sappaññe dhīrasammate; "
msgstr "—wise, esteemed as sages—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:13.3"
msgid "Saddhā ca nesaṃ sugate, "
msgstr "and whose faith in the Holy One "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:13.4"
msgid "mūlajātā patiṭṭhitā. "
msgstr "has roots planted deep, "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "an3.57:14.1"
msgid "Devalokañca te yanti, "
msgstr "they go to the realm of the gods, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:14.2"
msgid "kule vā idha jāyare; "
msgstr "or are born here in a good family. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:14.3"
msgid "Anupubbena nibbānaṃ, "
msgstr "Gradually those astute ones "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:14.4"
msgid "adhigacchanti paṇḍitā”ti. "
msgstr "reach extinguishment.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.57:14.5"
msgid "Sattamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

